In [66]:
#from the above graph, it is evident there is a positive/direct relationship between budget and revenue 
#because as the budget increases, the revenue also increase. From 1960, the fluctuations in budget triggered a similar effect 
#on the amount of revenue generated. For example, from the year 2000, when there was a sudden decline in budget allocatin, 
#revenue dropped. And as the budget allocation rose up again, the revenue increased as well. 

#Therefore, it can be concluded that as the budget for the movie increases, so does the revenue earning power of the movie

#Here, I am trying to see if there is a relationship between revenue and the director.(that is, 
#highest grossing directors) 


#In simple terms, do certain directors yield higher revenue compared to other directors. 
#so, I will do some filtering by seperating the top earning directors, top mid earning directors and bottom mid earning directors)
#and finally, bottom earning directors

top_revenue = df_tmdb.query('revenue > 1000000000').sort_values(by='revenue', ascending = False)
top_mid_revenue = df_tmdb.query('revenue >500000000' and 'revenue < 1000000000').sort_values(by= 'revenue', ascending = False)
bottom_mid_revenue = df_tmdb.query('revenue > 100000000' and 'revenue < 500000000').sort_values(by='revenue', ascending= False)
bottom_revenue = df_tmdb.query('revenue < 100000000').sort_values(by= 'revenue', ascending = False)
#top_revenue.shape()                                                         
    
    
#After filtering, we now sort the directors by how much Total revenue did they earn over time
top_grossers = top_revenue.groupby('revenue')['director'].sum()

top_mid_grossers = top_mid_revenue.groupby('revenue')['director'].sum()
bottom_mid_grossers = df_tmdb.groupby('revenue')['director'].sum()
bottom_grossers = df_tmdb.groupby('revenue')['director'].sum()


value = top_grossers.index

#I will show the outcome graphically using a pie chart
#top_grossers.value_counts().plot(kind = 'pie', figsize = (10, 10));  
plt.pie(value, labels = top_grossers, radius = 2);
plt.title('Chart of movie directors and their revenue stream', loc = 'center', pad = 100.7);
plt.legend(value, bbox_to_anchor=(1.85,1.025), loc='upper left');
